2\cf10 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The men of Ziph later went up to Saul at Gib\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ah and said: \u8220?Is not David hiding near us in the places difficult to approach at Ho\u697?resh, on the hill of Hac}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 h}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 i\u697?lah, which is south}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of J}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 shi\u697?mon?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Whenever it pleases you}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  to come down, O king, come, and we will surrender him into the hand of the king.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At this Saul said: \u8220?May you be blessed by Jehovah, for you have shown compassion to me. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Please go and try to find out exactly where he is and who saw him there, for I have been told that he is very cunning. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 23}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Carefully ascertain where all his hiding places are and return to me with the evidence. I will then go with you, and if he is in the land, I will search him out among all the thousands}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of Judah.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 24}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So they left and went to Ziph ahead of Saul, while David and his men were in the wilderness of Ma\u697?on, in the Ar\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 bah to the south of J}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 shi\u697?mon. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 25}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then Saul came with his men to look for him. When David was told, he at once went down to the crag and stayed in the wilderness of Ma\u697?on. When Saul heard this, he chased after David into the wilderness of Ma\u697?on. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 26}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?As Saul came to one side of the mountain, David and his men were on the other side of the mountain. David was hurrying to get away from Saul, but Saul and his men were closing in on David and his men to capture them. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 27}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But a messenger came to Saul, saying: \u8220?Come quickly, for the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines have made a raid on the land!\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 28}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At that Saul stopped chasing after David and went to confront the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines. That is why that place was named the Crag of the Divisions.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 29}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then David made his way up from there and stayed in the places difficult to approach at En-ged\u697?i.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 24\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?As soon as Saul returned from pursuing the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines, they told him: \u8220?Look! David is in the wilderness of En-ged\u697?i.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So Saul took 3,000 men chosen from all Israel and went to look for David and his men on the rocky cliffs of the mountain goats. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Saul came to the stone sheepfolds along the road, where there was a cave, and he went in to relieve himself}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  while David and his men were sitting in the recesses at the back of the cave. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David\u8217?s men said to him: \u8220?This is the day on which Jehovah is saying to you, \u8216?Look! I am giving your enemy into your hand, and you can do to him whatever seems good to you.\u8217?\u8221? So David rose up and quietly cut off the edge of Saul\u8217?s sleeveless coat. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But afterward David\u8217?s heart}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  kept striking him because he had cut off the edge of Saul\u8217?s sleeveless coat. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He said to his men: \u8220?It is unthinkable from Jehovah\u8217?s standpoint that I should do such a thing to my lord, the anointed of Jehovah, by lifting my hand against him, for he is the anointed of Jehovah.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So David restrained}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  his men with these words, and he did not allow them to attack Saul. As for Saul, he rose up from the cave and went on his way.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then David got up and went out from the cave and called out after Saul: \u8220?My lord the king!\u8221? When Saul looked behind him, David bowed down low with his face to the ground and prostrated himself. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David said to Saul: \u8220?Why do you listen to the words of men who say, \u8216?Look! David is seeking to harm you\u8217?? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?This very day your own eyes have seen how Jehovah gave you into my hand in the cave. But when someone said to kill you, I had pity on you and said, \u8216?I will not lift my hand against my lord, for he is the anointed of Jehovah.\u8217? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And look, my father, yes, see the edge of your sleeveless coat in my hand; for when I cut off the edge of your sleeveless coat, I did not kill you. You can now see and understand that I do not intend to harm you or to rebel, and I have not sinned against you, whereas you are hunting me down to take my life.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?May Jehovah judge between you and me, and may Jehovah take vengeance on you for me, but my hand will not come against you. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Just as the ancient proverb says, \u8216?From the wicked comes wickedness,\u8217? but my hand will not come against you. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?After whom has the king of Israel gone out? Whom are you chasing? A dead dog? A single flea? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?May Jehovah be the judge, and he will judge between you and me, and he will see and will plead my case and judge me and rescue me from your hand.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At the moment that David finished speaking these words to him, Saul said: \u8220?Is this your voice, my son David?\u8221? And Saul began to weep loudly. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He said to David: \u8220?You are more righteous than I am, for you have treated me well and I have repaid you with evil. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Yes, today you have told me of the good you did by not killing me when Jehovah surrendered me into your hand. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?For what man finds his enemy and sends him on his way unharmed? Jehovah will reward you with good because of what you have done for me today. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And now look! I know that you will surely rule as king and that in your hand the kingdom of Israel will endure. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now swear to me by Jehovah that you will not wipe out my descendants}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  after me and that you will not annihilate my name out of my father\u8217?s house.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So David swore to Saul, after which Saul went home. But David and his men went up to the stronghold.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 25\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?In time Samuel died; and all Israel gathered together to mourn for him and to bury him at his house in Ra\u697?mah. Then David rose and went down to the wilderness of Pa\u697?ran.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now there was a man in Ma\u697?on whose work was in Car\u697?mel.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  The man was very wealthy; he had 3,000 sheep and 1,000 goats, and he was then shearing his sheep at Car\u697?mel. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The man\u8217?s name was Na\u697?bal, and his wife\u8217?s name was Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail. The wife was discerning and beautiful, but the husband, a Ca\u697?le}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 b}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ite, was harsh, and he behaved badly. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David heard in the wilderness that Na\u697?bal was shearing his sheep. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So David sent ten young men to him, and David told the young men: \u8220?Go up to Car\u697?mel, and when you come to Na\u697?bal, ask him in my name about his welfare. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then say, \u8216?May you live long and may you be well}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and may your household be well and may all that you have be well. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now I hear that you are doing your shearing. When your shepherds were with us, we did not harm them, and they found nothing missing the whole time they were in Car\u697?mel. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Ask your young men, and they will tell you. May my young men find favor in your eyes, because we have come at a joyous time.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  Please give to your servants and to your son David whatever you can spare.\u8217?\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So David\u8217?s young men went and told all of this to Na\u697?bal in David\u8217?s name. When they finished, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Na\u697?bal answered David\u8217?s servants: \u8220?Who is David, and who is the son of Jes\u697?se? Nowadays many servants are breaking away from their masters. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Do I have to take my bread and my water and the meat that I butchered for my shearers and give it to men who come from who knows where?\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At that David\u8217?s young men returned and reported all these words to him. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David immediately said to his men: \u8220?Everyone strap on your sword!\u8221? So they all strapped on their swords, and David also strapped on his own sword, and about 400 men went up with David, while 200 men stayed with the baggage.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Meanwhile, one of the servants reported to Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail, Na\u697?bal\u8217?s wife: \u8220?Look! David sent messengers from the wilderness to wish our master well, but he screamed insults at them. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Those men were very good to us. They never harmed us, and we did not miss a single thing the whole time we were together with them in the fields. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?They were like a protective wall around us, both by night and by day, the whole time we were with them shepherding the flock. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now decide what you are going to do, for disaster has been determined against our master and against all his house, and he is such a worthless}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  man that no one can speak to him.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail quickly took 200 loaves of bread, two large jars of wine, five dressed sheep, five seah measures}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of roasted grain, 100 cakes of raisins, and 200 cakes of pressed figs and put all of it on the donkeys. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then she said to her servants: \u8220?Go on ahead of me; I will follow you.\u8221? But she said nothing to her husband Na\u697?bal.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?While she was riding on the donkey and going down under cover of the mountain, just then David and his men were coming down toward her, and she met them. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now David had been saying: \u8220?It was for nothing that I guarded everything that belongs to this fellow in the wilderness. Not a single thing belonging to him went missing, and yet he repays me evil for good. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?May God do the same and more to the enemies of David}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  if I allow a single male}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of his to survive until the morning.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 23}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail caught sight of David, she hurried down off the donkey and threw herself facedown before David, bowing to the ground. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 24}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?She then fell at his feet and said: \u8220?My lord, let the blame be on me; let your servant girl speak to you, and listen to the words of your servant girl. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 25}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Please, do not let my lord pay attention to this worthless Na\u697?bal, for he is just like his name. Na\u697?bal}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  is his name, and senselessness is with him. But I, your servant girl, did not see my lord\u8217?s young men whom you sent. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 26}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And now, my lord, as surely as Jehovah is living and as you are}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  living, it is Jehovah who has held you back from incurring bloodguilt and from taking revenge}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  with your own hand. May your enemies and those seeking injury to my lord become like Na\u697?bal. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 27}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now let this gift}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  that your servant girl has brought to my lord be given to the young men who are following my lord. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 28}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Pardon, please, the transgression of your servant girl, for Jehovah will without fail make for my lord a lasting house, because my lord is fighting the wars of Jehovah, and no evil has been found in you all your days. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 29}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When someone rises up to pursue you and seeks your life,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  the life}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of my lord will be wrapped securely in the bag of life with Jehovah your God, but the lives}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of your enemies he will hurl away like stones from a sling.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 30}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And when Jehovah has done for my lord all the good things he has promised and he appoints you as leader over Israel, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 31}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?you will have no remorse or regret}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  in your heart for shedding blood without cause and for letting the hand of my lord take revenge.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  When Jehovah confers good upon my lord, remember your servant girl.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 32}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At this David said to Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail: \u8220?Praise Jehovah the God of Israel, who sent you this day to meet me! }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 33}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And blessed be your good sense! May you be blessed for restraining me this day from incurring bloodguilt and from taking revenge}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  with my own hands. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 34}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Otherwise, as surely as Jehovah the God of Israel who held me back from harming you is living, if you had not come quickly to meet me, by morning there would not have remained a single male}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  belonging to Na\u697?bal.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 35}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?With that David accepted from her what she had brought him and said to her: \u8220?Go up in peace to your house. See, I have listened to you, and I will grant your request.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 36}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail later went back to Na\u697?bal, who was feasting like a king in his house, and Na\u697?bal}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  was in a good mood and was as drunk as could be. She did not tell him a single thing until the morning light. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 37}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?In the morning, when Na\u697?bal was sober, his wife told him these things. And his heart became like a dead man\u8217?s, and he lay paralyzed like a stone. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 38}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?About ten days later, Jehovah struck Na\u697?bal, and he died.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 39}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When David heard that Na\u697?bal had died, he said: \u8220?Praise Jehovah, who has pleaded my case of reproach from Na\u697?bal and has kept his servant from doing anything bad, and Jehovah has brought the badness of Na\u697?bal back on his own head!\u8221? Then David sent word to propose to Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail to take her as his wife. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 40}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So David\u8217?s servants came to Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail at Car\u697?mel and said to her: \u8220?David has sent us to you to take you as his wife.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 41}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?She immediately rose up and bowed with her face to the ground and said: \u8220?Here is your slave as a servant to wash the feet of the servants of my lord.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 42}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail quickly rose up and rode on her donkey with five of her female servants walking behind her; she accompanied the messengers of David and became his wife.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 43}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David had also married }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 hin\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 am from Jez\u697?r}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 el, and both women became his wives.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 44}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But Saul had given his daughter Mi\u697?chal, David\u8217?s wife, to Pal\u697?ti the son of La\u697?ish, who was from Gal\u697?lim.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 26\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?In time the men of Ziph came to Saul at Gib\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ah, saying: \u8220?Is David not hiding on the hill of Hac}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 h}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 i\u697?lah facing J}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 shi\u697?mon?\u8221?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So Saul rose up and went down to the wilderness of Ziph with 3,000 chosen men of Israel to look for David in the wilderness of Ziph. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Saul camped on the hill of Hac}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 h}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 i\u697?lah, which faces J}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 shi\u697?mon, by the road. David was then living in the wilderness, and he learned that Saul had come into the wilderness after him. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So David sent spies to verify that Saul had indeed come. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David later went to the place where Saul had encamped, and David saw the place where Saul and Ab\u697?ner the son of Ner, the chief of his army, were lying asleep; Saul lay asleep in the camp enclosure with the troops camping all around him. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then David said to }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 him\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lech the Hit\u697?tite and }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 bish\u697?ai the son of Z}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ru\u697?iah, the brother of Jo\u697?ab: \u8220?Who will go down with me into the camp to Saul?\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 bish\u697?ai replied: \u8220?I will go down with you.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So David and }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 bish\u697?ai made their way to the troops by night, and they found Saul lying asleep in the camp enclosure with his spear stuck into the ground next to his head; Ab\u697?ner and the troops were lying all around him.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 bish\u697?ai now said to David: \u8220?Today God has surrendered your enemy into your hand. And now, please, let me pin him to the ground with the spear just once, and I will not need to do it twice.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?However, David said to }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 bish\u697?ai: \u8220?Do not harm him, for who can lift his hand against the anointed of Jehovah and remain innocent?\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David continued: \u8220?As surely as Jehovah is living, Jehovah himself will strike him down, or his day will come and he will die, or he will go down into battle and perish. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?It is unthinkable from Jehovah\u8217?s standpoint for me to lift my hand against the anointed of Jehovah! So now take, please, the spear next to his head and the water jug, and let us be on our way.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So David took the spear and the water jug from next to Saul\u8217?s head, and they went away. No one saw or noticed them or woke up, for they were all asleep, because a deep sleep from Jehovah had fallen upon them. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then David crossed to the other side and stood on the top of the mountain some distance away, with a considerable space between them.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David called out to the troops and to Ab\u697?ner the son of Ner, saying: \u8220?Ab\u697?ner, will you not answer?\u8221? Ab\u697?ner answered: \u8220?Who are you who calls to the king?\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David said to Ab\u697?ner: \u8220?Are you not a man? And who is like you in Israel? So why did you not keep watch over your lord the king? For one of the soldiers came in to do away with your lord the king. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?What you have done is not good. As surely as Jehovah is living, you deserve to die, because you have not kept watch over your lord, the anointed of Jehovah. Now look around! Where are the king\u8217?s spear and the water jug that were next to his head?\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then Saul recognized the voice of David and said: \u8220?Is this your voice, my son David?\u8221? David replied: \u8220?It is my voice, my lord the king.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He added: \u8220?Why is my lord chasing after his servant, for what have I done, and what am I guilty of? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?My lord the king, please, listen to the words of his servant: If it is Jehovah who incited you against me, let him accept}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  my grain offering. But if men have incited you, they are cursed before Jehovah, because they have driven me away today from being united with Jehovah\u8217?s inheritance, saying, \u8216?Go, serve other gods!\u8217? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And now do not let my blood fall to the ground away from the presence of Jehovah, for the king of Israel has gone out to look for a single flea, as if he were chasing a partridge on the mountains.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?In turn Saul said: \u8220?I have sinned. Come back, my son David, for I will do you no more harm, because you regarded my life}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  as precious this day. Yes, I have acted foolishly and have made a terrible mistake.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David answered: \u8220?Here is the spear of the king. Let one of the young men come over and take it. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 23}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?It is Jehovah who will repay each one for his own righteousness and his own faithfulness, for today Jehovah gave you into my hand, but I was unwilling to lift my hand against the anointed of Jehovah. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 24}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Look! Just as your life}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  was precious to me this day, so may my life}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  be precious in the eyes of Jehovah, and may he rescue me out of all distress.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 25}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Saul replied to David: \u8220?May you be blessed, my son David. You will surely do great things, and you will surely prevail.\u8221? Then David went on his way, and Saul returned to his place.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 27\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?However, David said in his heart: \u8220?One day I will perish by Saul\u8217?s hand. The best thing for me is to escape to the land of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines; then Saul will give up looking for me in all the territory of Israel, and I will escape from his hand.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So David rose up with the 600 men who were with him and went over to A\u697?chish the son of Ma\u697?och, the king of Gath. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David stayed with A\u697?chish in Gath, he and his men, each man with his household. With David were his two wives, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 hin\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 am of Jez\u697?r}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 el and Ab\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 gail the Car\u697?me}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 l}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ite, Na\u697?bal\u8217?s widow. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When report was made to Saul that David had run away to Gath, he stopped searching for him.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then David said to A\u697?chish: \u8220?If I have found favor in your eyes, let them give me a place in one of the cities of the countryside, so that I may live there. Why should your servant live in the royal city with you?\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So A\u697?chish gave him Zik\u697?lag on that day. That is why Zik\u697?lag belongs to the kings of Judah down to this day.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The length of time}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  that David lived in the countryside of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines was a year and four months. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David would go up with his men to raid the Gesh\u697?u}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 r}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ites, the Gir\u697?zites, and the }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mal\u697?e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 k}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ites, for they were inhabiting the land that extended from Te\u697?lam as far as Shur and down to the land of Egypt. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When David would attack the land, he preserved neither man nor woman alive, but he took the flocks, herds, donkeys, camels, and clothing, after which he would return to A\u697?chish. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then A\u697?chish would ask: \u8220?Where did you make a raid today?\u8221? David would reply: \u8220?Against the south}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of Judah\u8221? or \u8220?Against the south of the J}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 rah\u697?m}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 l}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ites\u8221? or \u8220?Against the south of the Ken\u697?ites.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?David did not spare alive any man or woman to be brought to Gath, saying: \u8220?That they may not tell them about us and say, \u8216?This is what David did.\u8217?\u8221? (And that was his practice the whole time he lived in the countryside of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines.) }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So A\u697?chish believed David, saying to himself: \u8216?He has certainly become a stench among his people Israel, so he will always be my servant.\u8217?\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 28\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?In those days the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines assembled their armies for war against Israel. So A\u697?chish said to David: \u8220?You know, of course, that you and your men will go out into battle with me.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At that David said to A\u697?chish: \u8220?You surely know what your servant will do.\u8221? A\u697?chish said to David: \u8220?That is why I will appoint you as my permanent bodyguard.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now Samuel had died, and all Israel had mourned him and had buried him in Ra\u697?mah, his own city. And Saul had removed the spirit mediums and the fortune-tellers from the land.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines assembled and went and set up camp in Shu\u697?nem. So Saul assembled all Israel, and they set up camp in Gi}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 l}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 bo\u697?a. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When Saul saw the camp of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines, he was afraid, and his heart trembled greatly. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Although Saul would inquire of Jehovah, Jehovah never answered him, either in dreams or by the U\u697?rim or through the prophets. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Finally Saul said to his servants: \u8220?Find me a woman who is a spirit medium, and I will go and consult her.\u8221? His servants replied: \u8220?Look! There is a woman who is a spirit medium in En-dor.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So Saul disguised himself and put on other garments and went to the woman by night with two of his men. He said: \u8220?Use divination, please, by acting as a spirit medium, and bring up for me the one whom I designate to you.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?However, the woman said to him: \u8220?You must know what Saul did, how he removed the spirit mediums and the fortune-tellers from the land. Why, then, are you trying to trap me}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  to have me put to death?\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Saul then swore to her by Jehovah, saying: \u8220?As surely as Jehovah is alive, you will not incur any guilt in this matter!\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At this the woman said: \u8220?Whom should I bring up for you?\u8221? He replied: \u8220?Bring up Samuel for me.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When the woman saw \u8220?Samuel,\u8221?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  she cried out at the top of her voice and said to Saul: \u8220?Why did you trick me? You are Saul!\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The king said to her: \u8220?Do not be afraid, but what do you see?\u8221? The woman replied to Saul: \u8220?I see one like a god coming up out of the earth.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At once he asked her: \u8220?What does he look like?\u8221? to which she said: \u8220?It is an old man coming up, and he is clothed in a sleeveless coat.\u8221? At that Saul realized that it was \u8220?Samuel,\u8221? and he bowed low with his face to the ground and prostrated himself.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then \u8220?Samuel\u8221? said to Saul: \u8220?Why have you disturbed me by having me brought up?\u8221? Saul replied: \u8220?I am in great trouble. The Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines are fighting against me, and God has departed from me and no longer answers me, either through the prophets or in dreams; so that is why I am calling on you to let me know what I should do.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And \u8220?Samuel\u8221? said: \u8220?Why do you inquire of me now that Jehovah has departed from you and has become your adversary? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Jehovah will do for himself what he foretold through me: Jehovah will rip the kingdom out of your hands and give it to one of your fellow men, David. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Because you did not obey the voice of Jehovah and you did not execute his burning anger against the }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mal\u697?e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 k}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ites, that is why Jehovah is doing this to you this day. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Jehovah will also give both Israel and you into the hand of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines, and tomorrow you and your sons will be with me. Jehovah will also give the army of Israel into the hands of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At once Saul fell full length on the ground and became very much afraid because of \u8220?Samuel\u8217?s\u8221? words. And there was no strength left in him, because he had not eaten food all day and all night. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When the woman came to Saul and saw that he had been greatly disturbed, she said to him: \u8220?Here your servant has obeyed what you said, and I risked my life}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and did what you told me to do. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now, please, listen to what your servant has to say. Let me set before you a piece of bread; then eat so that you will have some strength to go on your way.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 23}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But he refused and said: \u8220?I am not going to eat.\u8221? However, his servants and also the woman kept urging him. Finally he listened to them and got up from the ground and sat on the bed. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 24}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The woman had a fattened calf in the house, so she quickly slaughtered}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  it and took flour and kneaded dough and baked it into unleavened bread. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 25}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?She served them to Saul and his servants, and they ate. After that they rose up and left during the night.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 29\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines assembled all their armies at A\u697?phek, while the Israelites were camping by the spring in Jez\u697?r}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 el. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And the lords of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines were passing by with their hundreds and their thousands, and David and his men were marching at the rear with A\u697?chish. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But the princes of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines said: \u8220?Why are these Hebrews here?\u8221? A\u697?chish replied to the princes of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines: \u8220?This is David, the servant of King Saul of Israel, who has been with me for a year or more. I have not found any fault in him from the day he deserted to me until today.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But the princes of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines became indignant at him, and they said to him: \u8220?Make the man go back. Let him return to the place where you assigned him. Do not let him go down with us into the battle, so that he will not turn against us during the battle. For what better way to put himself in favor with his lord than with the heads of our men? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Is this not the David about whom they sang when they danced, saying:\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi-432\li432 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf13 \u8216?Saul has struck down his thousands,\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf13 And David his tens of thousands\u8217??\u8221?\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So A\u697?chish summoned David and said to him: \u8220?As surely as Jehovah is living, you are upright, and I am pleased to have you go on the campaign with my army, for I have not found any fault with you from the day you came to me until today. But the lords do not trust you. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So return in peace, and do not do anything to displease the lords of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?However, David said to A\u697?chish: \u8220?Why, what have I done? What fault have you found in your servant from the day that I came to you until today? Why should I not come with you and fight against the enemies of my lord the king?\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?A\u697?chish answered David: \u8220?From my standpoint, you have been as good as an angel of God. But the princes of the Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 i}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 lis\u697?tines have said, \u8216?Do not let him go up with us into the battle.\u8217? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now get up early in the morning with the servants of your lord who came with you; rise up and leave early in the morning as soon as it is light.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\l